Explanation:

- The PATCH /admin/comments/{comment} route is provided by routes/admin.php via Route::resource('comments', ...) and maps to CommentController::update.
- The controller method signature is update(CommentsRequest $request, Comment $comment). The route contains a path parameter named {comment} which is an Eloquent model binding (ID in the URL).
- The request validation is defined in App\Http\Requests\Admin\CommentsRequest:
  - rules(): 'content' => 'required', 'posted_at' => 'required|after_or_equal:...','author_id' => 'required|exists:users,id'
  - prepareForValidation() parses posted_at into a Carbon datetime.
- Based on that, the PATCH endpoint accepts:
  - a required path parameter "comment" (integer ID).
  - a required JSON body with properties: content (string), posted_at (string, date-time), author_id (integer). All three are required by validation. posted_at has the additional semantic constraint that it must be after_or_equal the associated post's posted_at; author_id must exist in users.id.

